Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a drab-coloured pottery ribbed vessel, the fabric is relatively coarse and grey in section, faint traces of two lines of black-painted demotic text survive on the interior, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip and faint traces of a further seven lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393900) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393900)
